parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective 3rd gear pinion can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to grinding or growling noises, vibration, and potentially catastrophic crashes at high speeds.
symptoms: Grinding or growling noise in 3rd gear
vibration
lunging forward
transmission malfunction
inability to shift into 3rd gear
noise even in idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random stalling of the engine can cause the motorcycle to suddenly stop, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences, especially when riding at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
often when coming to a stop or when the engine is hot
making it difficult or impossible to control the motorcycle
and in some cases
causing the rider to fall or lose balance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The difficulty in starting the engine after stalling can leave the rider stranded, vulnerable, and at risk of further accidents or injuries, especially if the motorcycle is in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The engine is hard to start or fails to start after stalling
requiring repeated attempts or prolonged cranking
and in some cases
leaving the rider unable to restart the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the third gear in the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stumbles when shifting into third gear
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission slips or makes unusual noises
the vehicle stalls or dies when coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies when coming to a stop
the engine stalls or dies when decelerating
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the engine makes unusual noises or vibrations before stalling.
